reviews.review_text:
Standing on a Tower.. Glad to revisit this show
 it has been a few years.
I guess my question has to be:

a complete show------------check
excellent sound-------------double check
and it is 1973----------------check
How in the world does it not get 5 stars?

This is a hometown show from
the Greatest Rock N Roll Band ever
IN THEIR PRIME laying down 33 tunes.

Regarding some of the reviews of shows on the archive
Not that I don't learn a thing or two
from our more astute and studied reviewers
but sometimes it is just swell
to wuff, and howl like a fool.
"get up and dance, it won't ruin you" Weir

set1 -Just getting warmed up
-Promised, Deal, Jack Straw
T.L.E.O
 P.I.T.B Nitro powered set closer.

Set 2- nearly perfect
My favorites here is the extended jams 
(HCS, China>Rider)

Donna Jean kicks butt on
You Ain't Woman Enough

 Box of Rain-always challenging  (minor vocal miscue)

Phil has some great harmonies throughout show
sound is really good with a few minor AUD drop outs

"They kept on dancing, til that old moon went down"

Set 3-perfect as hippies ever gonna be in this life

How sweet is the Half Step
just like honey

A bit of a rogue Me & My Uncle

He's Gone has really blossomed 
from the early versions Europe 72
>Truckin>PHil bass>TOO (edgy space meltdown)>EYES
>SLIP into a China Doll
SUGAR MAGNOLIA-perhaps at it's zenith-73

Have I mentioned Jerry Garcia  🎩
E) CASEY JONES
Ken Lubkowski I will give this show 5 stars on it's 48th anniversary.  Thanks for analog tapes. Thank you Betty Cantor-Jackson and thank you Grateful Dead.

50 years ago OTD this tape was a pride and joy of my collection back in those days, and here it is in all is glory, extended tuning and everything. 
just one of the great shows.
The Cobra Debut of Garcia guitar The Cobra. Didn't play it much but you can hear its unique qualities.
